Note:
WASI Interface - WebAssembly System Interface (preview1) Integration

This file implements the WASI preview1 interface for Runa WebAssembly backend.
WASI provides a standardized set of system calls that WASM modules can import
to access host system resources (file I/O, stdout/stderr, exit codes, clocks).

WASI preview1 is the current stable standard. Every WASI function imported by
a WASM module must come from the "wasi_snapshot_preview1" module namespace.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Define WASI preview1 function signatures as WASM type entries
- Register WASI imports into a WASM module (adds to Import section)
- Emit WASI call sequences for file I/O (fd_read, fd_write, fd_close)
- Emit WASI call sequences for process control (proc_exit)
- Emit WASI call sequences for clock access (clock_time_get)
- Emit WASI call sequences for environment/args (args_get, environ_get)
- Maintain registry of imported WASI functions with their assigned indices

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- WASM modules cannot directly invoke system calls - they must go through WASI
- Correct WASI import registration is required for WASM modules to run in any
  WASI-compliant runtime (wasmtime, wasmer, Node.js with WASI, browser polyfills)
- Function type signatures must exactly match the WASI preview1 specification
- Import index tracking ensures generated code calls the correct function

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- WASI function identifier constants (one per WASI call)
- WasiRegistry structure tracking which WASI functions are imported
- Type signature emission for each WASI function
- Import entry emission for each registered WASI function
- High-level helpers for common patterns (write to stdout, exit with code)

Dependencies:
- wasm_encoder for module-level state and section building
- instruction_encoder for LEB128 and opcode byte emission
- MachineCode for output buffer operations
- Layout for memory allocation
- List for collection operations
:End Note

Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/wasm/wasm_encoder.runa" as WasmEncoder
Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/wasm/instruction_encoder.runa" as WasmInstr
Import "compiler/backend/machine_code/common/machine_code_interface.runa" as MachineCode
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WASI FUNCTION IDENTIFIER CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Note:
WASI preview1 function IDs. These are assigned by this file and used as keys
in the WasiRegistry to track which WASI functions the module imports.

They do NOT correspond to fixed external numbers - WASI functions are identified
by name (e.g. "wasi_snapshot_preview1.fd_write"). These IDs are purely internal
to our compiler for bookkeeping.
:End Note

Constant WASI_FN_FD_WRITE as Integer is 1         Note: Write to file descriptor (stdout, stderr, files)
Constant WASI_FN_FD_READ as Integer is 2          Note: Read from file descriptor (stdin, files)
Constant WASI_FN_FD_CLOSE as Integer is 3         Note: Close file descriptor
Constant WASI_FN_FD_SEEK as Integer is 4          Note: Seek within file
Constant WASI_FN_PROC_EXIT as Integer is 5        Note: Exit process with status code
Constant WASI_FN_CLOCK_TIME_GET as Integer is 6   Note: Get clock time (monotonic, realtime)
Constant WASI_FN_ARGS_GET as Integer is 7         Note: Get command-line arguments
Constant WASI_FN_ARGS_SIZES_GET as Integer is 8   Note: Get arg count and total buffer size
Constant WASI_FN_ENVIRON_GET as Integer is 9      Note: Get environment variables
Constant WASI_FN_ENVIRON_SIZES_GET as Integer is 10   Note: Get env count and buffer size
Constant WASI_FN_PATH_OPEN as Integer is 11       Note: Open file at path
Constant WASI_FN_RANDOM_GET as Integer is 12      Note: Fill buffer with random bytes
Constant WASI_FN_FD_FDSTAT_GET as Integer is 13   Note: Get fd metadata
Constant WASI_FN_FD_PRESTAT_GET as Integer is 14  Note: Get preopened directory info
Constant WASI_FN_FD_PRESTAT_DIR_NAME as Integer is 15  Note: Get preopened dir path

Note: Total number of WASI functions we support
Constant WASI_FN_COUNT as Integer is 15

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WASI VALUE TYPE CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Note: WASM value types used in WASI function signatures
Constant WASM_VAL_I32 as Integer is 127    Note: 0x7F in WASM binary
Constant WASM_VAL_I64 as Integer is 126    Note: 0x7E in WASM binary
Constant WASM_VAL_F32 as Integer is 125    Note: 0x7D in WASM binary
Constant WASM_VAL_F64 as Integer is 124    Note: 0x7C in WASM binary

Note: WASI errno values (returned as i32 from most WASI functions)
Constant WASI_ERRNO_SUCCESS as Integer is 0
Constant WASI_ERRNO_BADF as Integer is 8        Note: Bad file descriptor
Constant WASI_ERRNO_INVAL as Integer is 28      Note: Invalid argument
Constant WASI_ERRNO_IO as Integer is 29         Note: I/O error
Constant WASI_ERRNO_NOENT as Integer is 44      Note: No such file or directory

Note: Standard file descriptors
Constant WASI_FD_STDIN as Integer is 0
Constant WASI_FD_STDOUT as Integer is 1
Constant WASI_FD_STDERR as Integer is 2

Note: WASI clock IDs
Constant WASI_CLOCK_REALTIME as Integer is 0
Constant WASI_CLOCK_MONOTONIC as Integer is 1
Constant WASI_CLOCK_PROCESS_CPUTIME as Integer is 2
Constant WASI_CLOCK_THREAD_CPUTIME as Integer is 3

Note: WASI seek whence values
Constant WASI_WHENCE_SET as Integer is 0
Constant WASI_WHENCE_CUR as Integer is 1
Constant WASI_WHENCE_END as Integer is 2

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WASI REGISTRY STRUCTURE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
WasiRegistry tracks which WASI functions have been imported by the current
module. Each WASI function gets a stable import index assigned on first use.
The registry also tracks the corresponding type signature index so we can
emit the correct import entry later.

When code generation needs to call a WASI function, it calls wasi_get_import_index
which returns the function's assigned WASM function index (registering the
function if not already imported). Generated code then uses this index in a
WASM call instruction.

Memory layout (120 bytes, Tier 3 OWNED HEAP):
Offset 0:   module_state (pointer to WasmModuleState)
Offset 8:   import_indices (array of 15 i32, one slot per WASI function)
Offset 128: imported_count (number of WASI functions actually imported)
@End Reasoning

Type called "WasiRegistry":
    module_state as Integer
    import_indices as Integer
    imported_count as Integer
End Type

Note: ============================================================================
Note: REGISTRY CREATION AND DESTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "wasi_registry_create" that takes module_state as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Creates a new WASI registry bound to the given WasmModuleState.
    The registry starts empty; WASI functions will be registered on demand
    during code generation.
    @End Reasoning

    Let registry be proc allocate from Layout with 24
    If registry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Allocate import_indices array: 16 slots (WASI_FN_COUNT + 1 buffer) of 8 bytes each
    Let indices be proc allocate from Layout with 128
    If indices is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with registry
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Initialize all indices to -1 (not imported)
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 16:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with indices, i multiplied by 8, -1
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with registry, 0, module_state
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with registry, 8, indices
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with registry, 16, 0

    Return registry
End Process

Process called "wasi_registry_destroy" that takes registry as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Releases memory held by the registry. Does NOT free the module_state
    (owned elsewhere) or emitted import entries (owned by module_state).
    @End Reasoning

    If registry is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Let indices be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with registry, 8
    If indices is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with indices
    End If

    proc deallocate from Layout with registry
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WASI TYPE SIGNATURE EMISSION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Each WASI function has a fixed type signature defined by the WASI preview1 spec.
This process emits the bytes representing the function type signature into the
module's type section.

Type signature bytes (per WASM binary spec):
  0x60              Note: function type marker
  param_count       Note: LEB128-encoded number of parameters
  param_types...    Note: One byte per parameter (valtype)
  return_count      Note: LEB128-encoded number of return values
  return_types...   Note: One byte per return value (valtype)

WASI functions always return exactly one i32 (the errno).
Exception: proc_exit returns zero values (it doesn't return at all).
@End Reasoning

Process called "wasi_emit_type_signature" that takes module_state as Integer, wasi_fn as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emits type signature into the module's type section and returns the type index

    Note: Get parameter bytes for this WASI function
    Let params be proc allocate from Layout with 16
    If params is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If

    Let param_count be 0
    Let return_count be 1

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_WRITE:
        Note: fd_write(fd: i32, iovs: ptr, iovs_len: i32, nwritten: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 2, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 3, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 4
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_READ:
        Note: fd_read(fd: i32, iovs: ptr, iovs_len: i32, nread: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 2, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 3, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 4
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_CLOSE:
        Note: fd_close(fd: i32) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 1
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_SEEK:
        Note: fd_seek(fd: i32, offset: i64, whence: i32, newoffset: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I64
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 2, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 3, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 4
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_PROC_EXIT:
        Note: proc_exit(code: i32) -> never
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 1
        Set return_count to 0
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_CLOCK_TIME_GET:
        Note: clock_time_get(id: i32, precision: i64, time: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I64
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 2, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 3
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_ARGS_GET:
        Note: args_get(argv: ptr, argv_buf: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 2
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_ARGS_SIZES_GET:
        Note: args_sizes_get(argc: ptr, argv_buf_size: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 2
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_ENVIRON_GET:
        Note: environ_get(environ: ptr, environ_buf: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 2
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_ENVIRON_SIZES_GET:
        Note: environ_sizes_get(count: ptr, buf_size: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 2
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_PATH_OPEN:
        Note: path_open(fd, dirflags, path, path_len, oflags, fs_rights_base: i64,
        Note:           fs_rights_inheriting: i64, fdflags, opened_fd: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 2, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 3, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 4, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 5, WASM_VAL_I64
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 6, WASM_VAL_I64
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 7, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 8, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 9
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_RANDOM_GET:
        Note: random_get(buf: ptr, buf_len: i32) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 2
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_FDSTAT_GET:
        Note: fd_fdstat_get(fd: i32, buf: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 2
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_PRESTAT_GET:
        Note: fd_prestat_get(fd: i32, buf: ptr) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 2
    End If

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_PRESTAT_DIR_NAME:
        Note: fd_prestat_dir_name(fd: i32, path: ptr, path_len: i32) -> errno: i32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 0, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 1, WASM_VAL_I32
        proc memory_set_byte from Layout with params, 2, WASM_VAL_I32
        Set param_count to 3
    End If

    If param_count is equal to 0:
        Note: Unknown WASI function ID
        proc deallocate from Layout with params
        Return -1
    End If

    Note: Register the type signature in the module's type section
    Let type_index be proc add_function_type from WasmEncoder with module_state, params, param_count, return_count
    proc deallocate from Layout with params
    Return type_index
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: WASI IMPORT REGISTRATION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Registers a WASI function as an import in the module's import section if not
already registered. Returns the WASM function index to use in call instructions.

Import entries have the format:
  module_name     Note: always "wasi_snapshot_preview1"
  field_name      Note: WASI function name (e.g. "fd_write")
  import_kind     Note: 0x00 for function import
  type_index      Note: LEB128 type index

Because imports occur BEFORE function definitions in the WASM function index
space, the first imported WASI function gets function index 0, second gets 1,
etc. Actual user-defined functions get indices starting after all imports.
@End Reasoning

Process called "wasi_get_function_name" that takes wasi_fn as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns pointer to the null-terminated WASI function name string

    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_WRITE:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "fd_write"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_READ:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "fd_read"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_CLOSE:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "fd_close"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_SEEK:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "fd_seek"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_PROC_EXIT:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "proc_exit"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_CLOCK_TIME_GET:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "clock_time_get"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_ARGS_GET:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "args_get"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_ARGS_SIZES_GET:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "args_sizes_get"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_ENVIRON_GET:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "environ_get"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_ENVIRON_SIZES_GET:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "environ_sizes_get"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_PATH_OPEN:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "path_open"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_RANDOM_GET:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "random_get"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_FDSTAT_GET:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "fd_fdstat_get"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_PRESTAT_GET:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "fd_prestat_get"
    End If
    If wasi_fn is equal to WASI_FN_FD_PRESTAT_DIR_NAME:
        Return proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "fd_prestat_dir_name"
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "wasi_get_import_index" that takes registry as Integer, wasi_fn as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the WASM function index for the given WASI function, registering
    the import if it has not been registered yet. This is the primary entry
    point used by code generation when emitting a call to a WASI function.
    @End Reasoning

    If registry is equal to 0:
        Return -1
    End If

    If wasi_fn is less than 1:
        Return -1
    End If
    If wasi_fn is greater than WASI_FN_COUNT:
        Return -1
    End If

    Let indices be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with registry, 8
    Let slot_offset be wasi_fn multiplied by 8
    Let existing_index be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with indices, slot_offset

    If existing_index is not equal to -1:
        Note: Already imported - return existing index
        Return existing_index
    End If

    Note: Not yet imported - register it now
    Let module_state be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with registry, 0

    Let type_index be proc wasi_emit_type_signature with module_state, wasi_fn
    If type_index is equal to -1:
        Return -1
    End If

    Let module_name be proc string_literal from WasmEncoder with "wasi_snapshot_preview1"
    Let field_name be proc wasi_get_function_name with wasi_fn

    Let import_index be proc add_function_import from WasmEncoder with module_state, module_name, field_name, type_index

    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with indices, slot_offset, import_index

    Let imported_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with registry, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with registry, 16, imported_count plus 1

    Return import_index
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIGH-LEVEL WASI CALL EMITTERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
These helpers emit complete WASM instruction sequences for common WASI
operations. They handle argument setup, the call instruction, and any
required post-call error handling.

Each helper assumes the generated function has a linear memory buffer
available (standard WASM memory). Arguments and output buffers for WASI
calls must be placed in linear memory by the caller.
@End Reasoning

Process called "wasi_emit_call_fd_write" that takes registry as Integer, code_buf as Integer, fd as Integer, iovs_ptr as Integer, iovs_len as Integer, nwritten_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a call to fd_write with constant arguments
    Note: Stack after: errno (i32)

    Let import_index be proc wasi_get_import_index with registry, WASI_FN_FD_WRITE
    If import_index is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: i32.const fd
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, fd
    Note: i32.const iovs_ptr
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, iovs_ptr
    Note: i32.const iovs_len
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, iovs_len
    Note: i32.const nwritten_ptr
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, nwritten_ptr
    Note: call import_index
    proc emit_call from WasmInstr with code_buf, import_index

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "wasi_emit_call_fd_read" that takes registry as Integer, code_buf as Integer, fd as Integer, iovs_ptr as Integer, iovs_len as Integer, nread_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a call to fd_read. Stack after: errno (i32)

    Let import_index be proc wasi_get_import_index with registry, WASI_FN_FD_READ
    If import_index is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, fd
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, iovs_ptr
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, iovs_len
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, nread_ptr
    proc emit_call from WasmInstr with code_buf, import_index

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "wasi_emit_call_proc_exit" that takes registry as Integer, code_buf as Integer, exit_code as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a call to proc_exit. Does not return.

    Let import_index be proc wasi_get_import_index with registry, WASI_FN_PROC_EXIT
    If import_index is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, exit_code
    proc emit_call from WasmInstr with code_buf, import_index

    Note: proc_exit does not return - emit unreachable to satisfy type checker
    proc emit_unreachable from WasmInstr with code_buf

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "wasi_emit_call_clock_time_get" that takes registry as Integer, code_buf as Integer, clock_id as Integer, precision as Integer, time_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a call to clock_time_get. Stack after: errno (i32)
    Note: The time is written to memory at time_ptr as i64

    Let import_index be proc wasi_get_import_index with registry, WASI_FN_CLOCK_TIME_GET
    If import_index is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, clock_id
    proc emit_i64_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, precision
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, time_ptr
    proc emit_call from WasmInstr with code_buf, import_index

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "wasi_emit_call_random_get" that takes registry as Integer, code_buf as Integer, buf_ptr as Integer, buf_len as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Emit a call to random_get. Fills buf_ptr with random bytes.

    Let import_index be proc wasi_get_import_index with registry, WASI_FN_RANDOM_GET
    If import_index is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If

    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, buf_ptr
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, buf_len
    proc emit_call from WasmInstr with code_buf, import_index

    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONVENIENCE WRAPPERS FOR COMMON PATTERNS
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "wasi_emit_write_stdout" that takes registry as Integer, code_buf as Integer, data_ptr as Integer, data_len as Integer, iov_scratch_ptr as Integer, nwritten_scratch_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Emits code that writes a buffer to stdout via fd_write. WASI fd_write
    takes an iovec (pointer + length pair) in linear memory, not a raw buffer.

    Before emitting the call, we write the iovec into iov_scratch_ptr:
      iov_scratch_ptr[0] = data_ptr    (8 bytes - pointer as i32 in low 32 bits, padded)
      iov_scratch_ptr[8] = data_len

    Then we call fd_write(STDOUT, iov_scratch_ptr, 1, nwritten_scratch_ptr).

    The caller must have allocated iov_scratch_ptr (8 bytes) and
    nwritten_scratch_ptr (4 bytes) in linear memory.
    @End Reasoning

    Note: Store data_ptr at iov_scratch_ptr + 0 using i32.store
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, iov_scratch_ptr
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, data_ptr
    proc emit_i32_store from WasmInstr with code_buf, 2, 0

    Note: Store data_len at iov_scratch_ptr + 4 (standard WASI iovec_t layout in 32-bit WASM)
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, iov_scratch_ptr
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, data_len
    proc emit_i32_store from WasmInstr with code_buf, 2, 4

    Note: Call fd_write(STDOUT, iov_scratch_ptr, 1, nwritten_scratch_ptr)
    Return proc wasi_emit_call_fd_write with registry, code_buf, WASI_FD_STDOUT, iov_scratch_ptr, 1, nwritten_scratch_ptr
End Process

Process called "wasi_emit_write_stderr" that takes registry as Integer, code_buf as Integer, data_ptr as Integer, data_len as Integer, iov_scratch_ptr as Integer, nwritten_scratch_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Same as wasi_emit_write_stdout but writes to stderr (fd 2) instead of stdout.
    Useful for emitting error diagnostics from generated code.
    @End Reasoning

    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, iov_scratch_ptr
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, data_ptr
    proc emit_i32_store from WasmInstr with code_buf, 2, 0

    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, iov_scratch_ptr
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, data_len
    proc emit_i32_store from WasmInstr with code_buf, 2, 4

    Return proc wasi_emit_call_fd_write with registry, code_buf, WASI_FD_STDERR, iov_scratch_ptr, 1, nwritten_scratch_ptr
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: REGISTRY QUERIES
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "wasi_is_registered" that takes registry as Integer, wasi_fn as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns 1 if the given WASI function has been imported, 0 otherwise

    If registry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If wasi_fn is less than 1:
        Return 0
    End If
    If wasi_fn is greater than WASI_FN_COUNT:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let indices be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with registry, 8
    Let slot_offset be wasi_fn multiplied by 8
    Let existing_index be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with indices, slot_offset

    If existing_index is equal to -1:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "wasi_imported_count" that takes registry as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Returns the number of WASI functions currently registered
    If registry is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with registry, 16
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ERROR HANDLING HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Most WASI functions return an i32 errno value. These helpers emit common
error-checking patterns on the stack value left by a WASI call.
@End Reasoning

Process called "wasi_emit_check_errno_and_exit" that takes registry as Integer, code_buf as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: After a WASI call has left errno on the stack, this emits:
    Note:   if errno != 0: proc_exit(errno) ; unreachable
    Note: otherwise continue execution

    Note: Duplicate errno value so we can test and use it
    Note: local.tee is used to keep the value on the stack after storing

    Note: if errno != 0
    proc emit_i32_const from WasmInstr with code_buf, 0
    proc emit_i32_ne from WasmInstr with code_buf
    proc emit_if from WasmInstr with code_buf, 64

    Note: Emit proc_exit with errno as exit code
    Let import_index be proc wasi_get_import_index with registry, WASI_FN_PROC_EXIT
    If import_index is equal to -1:
        proc emit_end from WasmInstr with code_buf
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Put errno back on stack (it was consumed by the comparison, so
    Note: caller should have saved it in a local variable beforehand).
    Note: This helper assumes the caller left errno duplicated on the stack
    Note: so we just emit the call with a stack value of errno.
    proc emit_call from WasmInstr with code_buf, import_index
    proc emit_unreachable from WasmInstr with code_buf

    proc emit_end from WasmInstr with code_buf

    Return 1
End Process
